core.eeg.storage

Class MbtDataBuffering

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.eeg.storage.MbtDataBuffering

  • public class MbtDataBuffering
extends java.lang.Object
    MbtDataBuffering is responsible for storing and managing EEG raw data acquired in temporary buffers. Notifies MbtDataConversion when buffers are full, so that it can convert stored EEG raw data into user-readable data.

      • storePendingDataInBuffer

        public void storePendingDataInBuffer(byte[] data,
                                     int srcPos,
                                     int bufPos,
                                     int length)
        Stores a part of the EEG raw data inside the pendingRawData buffer when the maximum size of the buffer is reached This part begins at the [srcPos] position and the number of components stored is equal to the length argument. It is stored in the part of the destination array that begins at the [bufPos] position and ends at the [bufPos+length] position. In case packet size is too large for buffer, the overflow buffer is stored in a second buffer
        Parameters:
        data - the source raw EEG data array acquired by the headset and transmitted by Bluetooth to the application
        srcPos - the beginning position of the source EEG raw data array
        bufPos - the beginning position of the destination array (the pendingRawData buffer)
        length - the number of components from the source array to store into the pendingRawData buffer
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is raised if the source EEG data array is null or is empty
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - is raised if the number of elements to store is bigger than the size of the source array or bigger than the size of the destination array

      • storeOverflowDataInBuffer

        public void storeOverflowDataInBuffer(byte[] data,
                                      int srcPos,
                                      int bufPos,
                                      int length)
        Stores a part of the EEG raw data inside the oveflowBytes buffer in case packet size is too large for buffer As the overflowing data part is the part of the data source array that has not been stored in the pending data buffer, the beginning position is [srcPos + rawDataBufferSize - bufPos] and the number of components stored is equal to rawDataPacketSize - length. This part is stored in the part of the destination array that begins at the first position ([0]) and ends at the [rawDataPacketSize - length] position.
        Parameters:
        data - the source raw EEG data array acquired by the headset and transmitted by Bluetooth to the application
        srcPos - is the beginning position of the source EEG data array from where the first part of the data has been stored into the pending data buffer.
        bufPos - is the beginning position of the destination array (the pending buffer) within the first part of the data has been stored
        length - is the number of components from the source array to store into the oveflowBytes buffer
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is raised if the source EEG data array is null or is empty
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - is raised if the number of elements to store is bigger than the size of the source array or bigger than the size of the destination array
